    public class Incident
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    Represents an incident that can affect traffic.

      • Incident

        public Incident(long id,
        int version,
        int type,
        int severity,
        double latitude,
        double longitude,
        java.lang.Integer eventCode,
        boolean impacting,
        java.util.Date startTime,
        java.util.Date endTime,
        java.lang.String source,
        java.lang.String shortDescription,
        java.lang.String fullDescription,
        Incident.DelayImpact impact,
        Incident.Community community,
        GeoPoint head,
        java.util.Collection<GeoPoint> tails,
        java.util.Collection<GeoPoint> lastDetours,
        Incident.ParameterizedDescription paramDescription)
        Initializes a new instance of the Incident class with full data.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID associated with the incident.
        version - The version of the incident. (If the incident information is updated, the version number is incremented.)
        type - The type of incident: 1=Construction, 2=Event, 3=Flow, 4=Incident, 6 = Police.
        severity - The severity of the incident. This value can be in the range of 0-4, with 4 indicating the highest severity.
        latitude - The latitude of the incident.
        longitude - The longitude of the incident.
        eventCode - The AlertC event code associated with the incident.
        impacting - Whether the incident is impacting traffic.
        startTime - When the incident starts.
        endTime - When the incident ends.
        source - The source of the information.
        shortDescription - A short textual description of the incident.
        fullDescription - A longer textual description of the incident.
        impact - The delay impact.
        community - If community-reported, the community that reported it.
        head - Location of the farthest point on the road where the incident "starts".
        tails - Locations of the points behind the head where the incident ends.
        lastDetours - Locations of the last detour points to avoid the incident.
